narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Basic Calc 2 skills are covered in this course. There was a lot covered, but overall it was pretty manageable.
I learned all the material of Calc 2.
challenging class
I continued my knowledge in calculus 2. This course required a lot of outside preparation to understand what was going on in class.
Intense version of AP BC Calculus

The course helped develop the tools I can use to solve different integrals by going through a big variety of methods.

I have also never learned much about series convergence so this was new knowledge to me.
From this course, I learned how to effectively collaborate on math problem sets and to use outside resources to support what I am learning in class.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course covers a lot of material, and I think it is important that students go to office hours/seek additional help should they feel not so sure about a given topic. It is definitely pretty easy to fall behind if you do not do so.

Strengths: good curriculum, huge amount of resources to review learn the material
Weaknesses: depends on who is your instructor, some are better than other

Strengths: Exams had a lot of support.
Weaknesses: Problem Sets on the week of exams, and the general way it was taught made it hard to engage.

This class was very fast-paced and a lot of the content felt rushed. Because it was taught by so many different teachers, there was a big difference in teaching quality between me and many of my peers.
go over the p set material before we have to do the p set
I found this course very difficult to keep up with. I felt I was not learning the concepts well enough in class and that made it difficult to complete problem sets with full understanding.
Strengths were that the psets were very well made. Weaknesses was the difference in teaching between the different teachers.
The order that the material was taught in did not facilitate understanding of concepts.
I thought the online resources for this course were really good, especially with the videos on canvas since it gave you the groundwork for the material we were learning in class.

Strengths: organized notes. received helpful feedback

Weakness: slightly less engaging
weaknesses: way too much material covered and problem sets did not really help with the exam material

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would. I think it is an important class for many different majors/careers.
Yes, if you need the class as a pre-req or want to learn Calc 2. It is a solid Yale math course.
Yes, you need the content.
yes
I would recommend this course to another student if they have a good instructor.
If this is a prerec (it probably will be) then take it, its solid. Otherwise what are you doing
no, unless the student was placed into a section taught by certain (good) grad students, or the course head
This was not my favorite class, as I found the material somewhat unengaging. However, I do believe it is an important class in terms of forming a foundation in math.
no, if you can avoid it simply do not take it
